CFI_dim_t dim[];            unsigned char f18Addendum;  size_t len,offset;          intptr_t intel_flags;
                            CFI_dim_t dim[];            int64_t *dtp;               intptr_t intel_reserved1;
                                                        void *sig;                  intptr_t intel_reserved2;
                                                        void *reserved;             CFI_dim_t dim[];
                                                        int64_t ireserved;
                                                        CFI_dim_t dim[];
```

Probably the typedefs `CFI_rank_t`, `CFI_attribute_t`, ..., are also of different width among implementations. 

The ABI compatibility is discussed in https://github.com/j3-fortran/fortran_proposals/issues/247 and the [Discourse thread](https://fortran-lang.discourse.group/t/is-iso-fortran-binding-h-compatible-for-different-fortran-abis/2652/7).
